<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="110" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Herb, annual or rarely perennial, achlorophyllous, holoparasitic. Stems fleshy. Leaves reduced to scale-like bracts. Inflorescences terminal racemes, spikes, corymbs, or panicles. Calyx 5-toothed. Corolla sympetalous, bilabiate to regular, tubular and often curved. Style long, stigma crateriform and peltate, or bilamellar. Fruit loculicidal capsules.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="110">About 22 species: 18 in North America, 4 in South America.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
